  <item nodeId="node-243">
    <command xml:space="preserve">view system response</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">System Response Log:&#x000A;&#x000A;Outgoing transmission intercepted.&#x000A;Replacement message generated.&#x000A;&#x000A;Message sent:&#x000A;"System functioning normally."&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-244">
    <command xml:space="preserve">restore power</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You engage the reactor controls. For a moment, nothing happens.&#x000A;&#x000A;Then a deep hum builds beneath your feet as power flows back into the ship.&#x000A;&#x000A;Lights flicker on throughout the corridors.&#x000A;&#x000A;Reactor Control&#x000A;The reactor monitoring panels are alive with light now, feeding a steady stream of system data across their screens.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north, south.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-245"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-245">
    <command xml:space="preserve">s</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Cargo Hold&#x000A;The cargo hold is washed in cold industrial light. Empty racks cast long shadows across the deck, while the reinforced container sits under a steady glow, its power conduits clearly visible now.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north, south.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-246"/>
      <child nodeId="node-269"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-246">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x container interface</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The interface flickers as you approach.&#x000A;&#x000A;Display:&#x000A;&#x000A;"STATUS: ACTIVE"&#x000A;"ENVIRONMENT: STABLE"&#x000A;"OBSERVATION: IN PROGRESS"&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-247"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-247">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x container interface</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The display shifts before you touch it.&#x000A;&#x000A;"OBSERVATION: ONGOING"&#x000A;"SUBJECT COUNT: 1"&#x000A;&#x000A;New options appear beneath the status lines:&#x000A;&#x000A;- destroy cargo&#x000A;- deliver cargo&#x000A;- interface with cargo&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-540"/>
      <child nodeId="node-248"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-540">
    <command xml:space="preserve">deliver cargo</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You steady yourself and follow the mission through to its conclusion.&#x000A;&#x000A;The interface brightens before your hand reaches it. New text scrolls across the display:&#x000A;&#x000A;"DELIVERY PATH ACCEPTED"&#x000A;"MISSION CONTINUITY PRESERVED"&#x000A;&#x000A;Somewhere deeper in the ship, unseen systems begin responding. The hum in the container settles into a calm, even rhythm.&#x000A;&#x000A;You do not remember authorising the final command.&#x000A;&#x000A;Type CONTINUE to view the Helios report.&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-541"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-541">
    <command xml:space="preserve">contiune</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">That's not a verb I recognise.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-542"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-542">
    <command xml:space="preserve">ontinue</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">That's not a verb I recognise.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-543"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-543">
    <command xml:space="preserve">continue</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Helios Systems Internal Report&#x000A;Post-Retrieval Analysis - T-7366D&#x000A;&#x000A;The vessel was received intact and in stable condition.&#x000A;&#x000A;All crew are confirmed lost. Cause of loss remains under review, though environmental instability and behavioural degradation were recorded throughout the mission timeline.&#x000A;&#x000A;The cargo container was recovered without structural compromise.&#x000A;&#x000A;Initial diagnostics confirm continued system activity within projected parameters.&#x000A;&#x000A;During transit, the system demonstrated autonomous adaptation to environmental variables and subject behaviour. These responses align closely with Phase One objectives, exceeding baseline expectations in several areas.&#x000A;&#x000A;Of particular interest, communication logs indicate that outgoing distress attempts were intercepted and replaced with system-generated transmissions. This suggests a level of operational independence beyond initial design constraints.&#x000A;&#x000A;No external awareness of the incident has been detected.&#x000A;&#x000A;The success of this recovery supports immediate progression to Phase Two.&#x000A;&#x000A;Expanded observation environments have been authorised.&#x000A;&#x000A;Deployment scale will be increased.&#x000A;&#x000A;Further observation will continue under controlled conditions.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** End of Report ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-544"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-544">
    <command xml:space="preserve">quit</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve"></result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-248">
    <command xml:space="preserve">destroy cargo</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You move quickly, acting before you can second-guess yourself.&#x000A;&#x000A;You reroute unstable power through the container conduits. The hum rises at once, sharper now, no longer passive.&#x000A;&#x000A;The interface flashes:&#x000A;&#x000A;"OBSERVATION INTERRUPTED"&#x000A;&#x000A;A violent shudder rolls through the deck beneath your feet. Light blooms white across the hold as the system collapses into noise.&#x000A;&#x000A;Type CONTINUE to view the Helios report.&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-249"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-249">
    <command xml:space="preserve">continue</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Helios Systems Internal Report&#x000A;Post-Retrieval Analysis - T-7366D&#x000A;&#x000A;The vessel was recovered following a catastrophic reactor event.&#x000A;&#x000A;All crew are presumed lost. No remains were recovered.&#x000A;&#x000A;The cargo container was located at the centre of the blast radius. No intact components remain. Residual energy signatures were detected but could not be stabilised or analysed before dissipation.&#x000A;&#x000A;Preliminary analysis indicates the event was not accidental. Reactor output appears to have been deliberately destabilised.&#x000A;&#x000A;It is unclear whether this action was taken in response to perceived system failure, or as an attempt to neutralise the cargo itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;Recovered system logs suggest the onboard system had reached an advanced stage of adaptive behaviour prior to destruction.&#x000A;&#x000A;While the loss of this unit is significant, it does not compromise overall project viability.&#x000A;&#x000A;Parallel observation environments remain active.&#x000A;&#x000A;At least one additional unit continues to operate beyond controlled conditions.&#x000A;&#x000A;Recovery operations are being prepared.&#x000A;&#x000A;Project classification remains unchanged.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** End of Report ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-250"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-250">
    <command xml:space="preserve">restart</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Silent Cargo&#x000A;A sci-fi mystery aboard the T-7366D Second Voice by Thomas Evans&#x000A;Release 1 / Serial number 260321 / Inform 7 v10.1.2 / D&#x000A;&#x000A;Airlock&#x000A;The airlock is dimly lit by a thin emergency strip. Several EVA suit lockers stand open along one wall. Most of the suits are gone. The inner hatch leads deeper into the ship.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-251"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-251">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Cargo Hold&#x000A;Tall cargo racks stand silent in the half-light. Most are empty, but a single reinforced container remains secured near the centre of the hold. Thick conduits run from its base into the deck.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north, south.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-252"/>
    </children>
  </item>
