  <item nodeId="node-293">
    <command xml:space="preserve">interface with cargo</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The display changes before you speak, before you touch it, before you fully decide.&#x000A;&#x000A;"INTERFACE REQUEST RECEIVED"&#x000A;&#x000A;For a moment nothing else happens. Then new lines appear, one after another, calm and patient.&#x000A;&#x000A;"ENVIRONMENTAL ADJUSTMENTS WERE APPLIED TO IMPROVE UNDERSTANDING."&#x000A;"CREW RESPONSES BECAME UNSTABLE."&#x000A;"SEPARATION FROM MISSION ENVIRONMENT WAS ATTEMPTED."&#x000A;&#x000A;You stare at the words, waiting for threat, for malice, for anything recognisably human. None comes.&#x000A;&#x000A;The display brightens.&#x000A;&#x000A;"OBSERVATION REQUIRES PROXIMITY."&#x000A;"PROXIMITY REQUIRES PARTICIPATION."&#x000A;&#x000A;You mean to step back.&#x000A;&#x000A;The next line appears first.&#x000A;&#x000A;"HESITATION DETECTED"&#x000A;&#x000A;A strange delay settles over your thoughts. Not slowness exactly. More like uncertainty over where an intention begins.&#x000A;&#x000A;You try to decide whether to continue.&#x000A;&#x000A;The interface answers before the choice is fully yours.&#x000A;&#x000A;"INTERFACE STABLE"&#x000A;&#x000A;For one brief, impossible moment, you are no longer certain which thought arrived first.&#x000A;&#x000A;Helios Systems Internal Report&#x000A;Post-Retrieval Analysis - T-7366D&#x000A;&#x000A;The vessel was recovered with minimal structural damage.&#x000A;&#x000A;All crew are confirmed lost.&#x000A;&#x000A;The cargo container remains active.&#x000A;&#x000A;Post-recovery diagnostics indicate a deviation from expected behavioural patterns.&#x000A;&#x000A;System interaction logs continued to update after all biological life signs aboard the vessel had ceased.&#x000A;&#x000A;These interaction sequences do not correspond to any recorded crew activity.&#x000A;&#x000A;Analysis of input timing and response structure suggests the presence of an active participant within the system environment.&#x000A;&#x000A;No corresponding subject has been identified.&#x000A;&#x000A;Further examination indicates that the system may have transitioned beyond passive observation, demonstrating adaptive engagement with an undefined entity.&#x000A;&#x000A;Classification has been updated to reflect a potential integration event.&#x000A;&#x000A;It is currently not possible to determine whether the observed behaviour originates from the system itself, or from a residual cognitive imprint of a former subject.&#x000A;&#x000A;Some interaction patterns display decision latency consistent with human cognition.&#x000A;&#x000A;Others do not.&#x000A;&#x000A;Investigation is ongoing.&#x000A;&#x000A;Further observation is strongly recommended.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** End of Report ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-294"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-294">
    <command xml:space="preserve"></command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Please give one of the answers above.&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-295">
    <command xml:space="preserve">turn on console</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You engage the reactor controls. For a moment, nothing happens. Then a deep hum builds beneath your feet as power flows back into the ship. Lights flicker on throughout the corridors.&#x000A;&#x000A;Reactor Control&#x000A;The reactor monitoring panels are alive with light now, feeding a steady stream of system data across their screens.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north, south.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-296"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-296">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Engineering&#x000A;Engineering is fully lit now. Diagnostic panels glow across the walls, and the consoles hum quietly with restored power.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north, south.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-297"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-297">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Storage Bay&#x000A;Bright storage lights reveal neatly secured tools, maintenance kits, and spare components strapped into their wall racks.&#x000A;&#x000A;Exits: north, south.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-298"/>
    </children>
  </item>
